[03:13.64]	And hardly shall I carry out my side,
[03:16.47]	Her husband being alive. Now then we'll use
[03:19.70]	His countenance for the battle; which being done,
[03:23.25]	Let her who would be rid of him devise
[03:26.21]	His speedy taking off. As for the mercy
[03:29.17]	Which he intends to Lear and to Cordelia,
[03:32.26]	The battle done, and they within our power,
